4 (c) Information concerning the insurance agreement is not by reason of disclosure admissible in
5 evidence at trial.
6
7 (d) For the purposes of this section, an application for insurance may not be treated as part of an
8 insurance agreement.
9 (4) Disclosure of information by an insurer pursuant to subsection (1) must be made in accordance
10 with the provisions of the Insurance Information and Privacy Protection Act, Title 33, chapter 19.
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
13 integral part of Title 27, chapter 1, part 2, and the provisions of Title 27, chapter 1, part 2, apply to [section 1].
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
